Look Frasier, I've been getting a lot of complaints from sponsors saying that their ads are getting buried in huge commercial blocks.

01:30.500 --> 01:31.541
I see.

01:31.541 --> 01:35.013
So instead of having four blocks per hour we're going to have eight...

01:35.013 --> 01:38.817
...only they're only going to be half as long.  I thought it might help you.

01:38.817 --> 01:43.798
And you want to stay on top, don't you, Frasier?

01:43.798 --> 01:45.737
...Frasier?

01:45.737 --> 01:49.351
Of course, very much so, yes!

01:49.351 --> 01:51.059
Good.

01:54.527 --> 01:56.559
Frasier, what was that?

01:56.559 --> 01:57.282
What was what?

01:57.282 --> 02:02.598
Call me crazy, but when you were talking to Kate you had this goofy little teenage look on your face.

02:02.598 --> 02:05.510
If I didn't know better, I'd swear you got a thing for her.

02:05.510 --> 02:06.250
For Kate?

02:06.250 --> 02:07.884
mm-hmm.  Look at you.  You're flushed.

02:07.884 --> 02:10.907
I had Mexican for lunch.

02:10.907 --> 02:14.646
It's not lust ?it's a Chimichanga.

02:14.646 --> 02:18.223
Frasier, I'm sorry but I'm never wrong about these things.

02:18.223 --> 02:20.014
Have you lost your mind?

02:20.014 --> 02:23.767
Look me in the eye and tell me I'm wrong.

02:23.767 --> 02:26.446
Roz, you're wrong.

02:26.446 --> 02:29.320
Oh my God.  I'm sitting on a powder-keg here.

02:29.320 --> 02:31.361
You've got a crush on Kate!

02:31.361 --> 02:33.713
Stop it.

02:33.713 --> 02:37.300
Everybody knows you are the biggest gossip in the entire station.  You'll be sworn to secrecy.

02:37.300 --> 02:38.810
I swear I won't tell anyone.

02:38.810 --> 02:40.579
No, it doesn't count until you shake my hand.

02:40.579 --> 02:41.705
Oh, all right.

02:41.705 --> 02:44.248
Roz, Kate and I...

02:44.248 --> 02:52.811
Oh my God!  Kate's "Dirty Girl"!

02:52.811 --> 02:57.555
Kate is the woman you had sex with on the air in this booth and you were calling "Dirty Girl"?

02:57.555 --> 03:01.859
Oh my God!

03:01.859 --> 03:04.432
I just need a minute here...
Alright.

03:04.432 --> 03:08.049
Of course it happened months ago.  Only a couple of times.

03:08.049 --> 03:09.166
Roz: Uh-huh.

03:09.166 --> 03:16.745
Our relationship started out so antagonistic.  Then suddenly it just spilled over into passion.  Intense, romantic, exciting...

03:16.745 --> 03:22.162
...the whole thing's over now, but Roz, you will say nothing, absolutely nothing...

03:22.162 --> 03:24.352
Roz?  Roz?

03:24.352 --> 03:27.634
Boy, I'll never do that again!

03:34.546 --> 03:37.751
I notice you're grating that carrot at a 45-degree angle.

03:37.751 --> 03:39.341
Does that enhance the flavour?

03:39.341 --> 03:44.696
No, no.  Just an old habit.

03:44.696 --> 03:47.103
And why exactly did you choose to grate carrots?

03:47.103 --> 03:51.066
Because we have carrots!

03:52.825 --> 03:58.184
I hope you don't mind all the questions.  It's just now that I'm separated I'm going to have to learn to cook for myself.

03:58.184 --> 04:02.824
Quite alright.  Tell you what.  Why don't you grate while I put the chicken in?

04:09.520 --> 04:17.253
Thousands of little metal teeth able to tear the flesh right off your...

04:18.841 --> 04:26.506
No, no, false alarm.  Normally I bleed like the Russian royal Family, but not today.

04:26.506 --> 04:29.518
That's Interesting.  You put a toothpick in that chicken.

04:29.518 --> 04:30.943
Now, is that to check when it's done?

04:30.943 --> 04:36.909
No, no.  I'm just marking which one is yours.

04:36.909 --> 04:39.269
Dr. Crane, would you mind setting the table?

04:39.269 --> 04:43.392
Oh, certainly.  Just give a yell if there's anything else that you need to have grated.

04:43.392 --> 04:46.400
You've done enough grating for one night!

04:50.548 --> 04:53.074
Writing a letter?

04:53.792 --> 04:56.239
No, I'm writing my memoirs!

04:56.239 --> 04:57.779
I'll take that as a Yes.

04:57.779 --> 04:59.955
My old army buddy.

04:59.955 --> 05:03.111
You know that's the improper use of a hyphen.

05:03.111 --> 05:07.633
Somehow I don't think Maurie Dingman will mind.

05:07.633 --> 05:13.000
Then I'm sure he won't notice that missing comma and that run-on sentence.

05:13.000 --> 05:20.140
Although this is a particularly glaring error.  It's best not to end a sentence with a preposition.

05:25.153 --> 05:29.971
Not to be technical, but "Off" is a preposition too!

05:33.588 --> 05:34.543
Evening all.

05:34.543 --> 05:38.180
Good news.  I have tickets for the symphony tomorrow night.  Are you free?

05:38.180 --> 05:40.349
Well, actually no.  I have a date.

05:40.349 --> 05:41.406
With who?

05:41.406 --> 05:43.661
Some woman I met at my accountant's.

05:43.661 --> 05:45.487
Yeah, when I was in the service ?

05:45.487 --> 05:54.828
first thing I'd do when I hit a new port was go straight to an accountant and find out where the action was.

05:54.828 --> 05:58.490
I must admit I'm having a little trouble working up my enthusiasm about it.

05:58.490 --> 06:02.853
Only the woman's fault.  It's just that I find myself preoccupied with somebody else right now.

06:02.853 --> 06:08.981
Well, frankly, it's gone a bit beyond preoccupation.
I'm having fantasies about her all the time.

06:08.981 --> 06:11.039
Well there's nothing wrong with that.

06:11.039 --> 06:20.815
You know, when I first met your mother she was so upbeat and bouncy I used to fantasize about her
wearing a skimpy little cheerleader's outfit, shaking her pom-poms...

06:20.815 --> 06:22.981
Grow up you two!

06:22.981 --> 06:25.710
I'm just saying it's perfectly natural.

06:25.710 --> 06:32.064
I can't tell you the number of times I was on a stake-out in the cold picturing your mother
in front of a warm fire wearing nothing but a...

06:32.064 --> 06:34.719
Frasier/Niles: DAD!!!

06:34.719 --> 06:37.812
Oh, I'm sorry.  One day your mother and I went on a church picnic

06:37.812 --> 06:42.529
and the two of you came floating down the river in little wicker baskets!

06:42.529 --> 06:44.919
Was that so hard?

06:46.722 --> 06:50.647
You know, I'm beginning to wonder if I have real feelings for this woman?

06:50.647 --> 06:52.976
I mean I think about her all the time.

06:52.976 --> 06:57.009
Ooh this sounds interesting.  Who are we talking about?

06:57.009 --> 06:57.793
Kate from the office.

06:57.793 --> 07:02.214
Oh, "Dirty Girl."

07:02.214 --> 07:03.348
She seemed nice.

07:03.348 --> 07:06.960
She is nice.  Intelligent, accomplished.

07:06.960 --> 07:09.472
Well, if you think so much of her why don't you ask her out?

07:09.472 --> 07:11.810
Well, we agreed we wouldn't pursue things.

07:11.810 --> 07:17.072
Frankly, she hasn't given me any indication since that she's even had a second thought about me.

07:17.072 --> 07:22.114
Added to which, if Frasier did pursue her and she rejected him, he could hardly rationalise it by saying

07:22.114 --> 07:32.827
she doesn't know what she's missing.  She would know exactly what she's missing - she just didn't miss it!

07:32.827 --> 07:34.981
Thank you, Niles!

07:34.981 --> 07:38.745
You can't let fear of rejection stop you Dr. Crane.

07:38.745 --> 07:41.612
Well, you know Daphne, it's just not that easy really.

07:41.612 --> 07:44.397
Maybe I'm letting this romantic fantasy run away with me.

07:44.397 --> 07:46.836
Truth is we don't really know each other very well and,

07:46.836 --> 07:51.499
you know what if she did reject me, I'd end up going to work every day feeling like a fool.

07:51.499 --> 07:53.274
Hey, am I getting a whiff of chicken here?

07:53.274 --> 07:58.606
Oh fine Dad!  Frankly I've had enough of you and your adolescent wisecracks.

07:58.606 --> 08:01.001
I am not "chicken."  I am just merely hesitant.

08:01.001 --> 08:05.438
alright! I will ask her out tomorrow.  Fine.  I hope that makes you happy!

08:05.438 --> 08:09.078
I just thought I smelled dinner!

08:12.843 --> 08:15.879
THE CITY WITH BROAD, BARE SHOULDERS

08:15.879 --> 08:18.837
Oh Kate.  Hi.  There you are.  I wanted to talk with you.

08:18.837 --> 08:21.282
I'm just going down to the Billing department.

08:21.282 --> 08:26.342
I'll ride along with you.

08:30.955 --> 08:40.116
You know, it seems every time we speak lately the conversation always leads to ratings, commercials, demographics...

08:40.116 --> 08:45.784
...hirings and firings, promotions, demotions, the odd skirmish over the expense account.

08:45.784 --> 08:50.611
It just seems all so dry and impersonal.

08:50.611 --> 08:52.095
Did I hit the right button?

08:52.095 --> 08:56.131
Oh, yes!

08:56.131 --> 08:58.586
Yes.  Yeah.  You did.  You did.  You hit the right button.

08:58.586 --> 09:02.125
I'm sorry ?I've got a lot on my mind.

09:02.125 --> 09:04.183
Yeah, so do I.

09:04.183 --> 09:06.915
Kate I wanted to ask you?

09:06.915 --> 09:11.402
Frasier, I'm leaving KACL.  I'm moving to Chicago.

09:11.402 --> 09:12.279
What?

09:12.279 --> 09:15.228
Yeah.  I'm taking over a station there.

09:15.228 --> 09:23.620
In fact I'm going out on the "Redeye" tonight.  I thought, given our history, I should tell you first.

09:23.620 --> 09:27.688
Well, I'm at a loss for words.

09:27.688 --> 09:32.962
Wouldn't you know it ?on the day I'm leaving?

09:34.220 --> 09:38.166
Well congratulations.  This is a big step for you.

09:38.166 --> 09:42.398
Thanks.  Boy, this was not an easy decision believe me.

09:42.398 --> 09:45.899
You never know if you're leaving a place too soon.

09:45.899 --> 09:54.059
All I know is that for the time you've been here I've certainly enjoyed having you.

09:54.059 --> 10:02.148
Having you...
I know.

10:02.148 --> 10:04.752
I guess this is goodbye.

10:04.752 --> 10:08.496
I suppose so.

10:08.496 --> 10:10.557
Goodbye, Kate.

