If she were to ask you that one, what would you say?

11:04.140 --> 11:08.538
"Cheque please" comes to mind!

11:10.512 --> 11:12.813
Hello?

11:12.813 --> 11:16.861
Niles, no one was mean to you last night.

11:16.861 --> 11:20.222
No, if you want to come over, that's great.  Yeah, we'd love to see you.

11:20.222 --> 11:23.790
OK.  Bye.

11:23.790 --> 11:25.937
Hey Niles.

11:26.932 --> 11:29.034
No traffic?

11:29.034 --> 11:31.895
Dad, you sounded lonely so I rented some movies.

11:31.895 --> 11:34.283
Oh, didn't you know the VCR is broken?

11:34.283 --> 11:35.268
No subtitles this time!

11:35.268 --> 11:38.154
Oh, that's right, I got it fixed.

11:38.154 --> 11:39.199
What'd you bring?

11:39.199 --> 11:42.182
I have "The Way We Were" and a classic, "Casablanca."

11:42.182 --> 11:44.753
Oh, I just love that movie.

11:44.753 --> 11:53.842
Is there any more heartbreaking moment in all of film than when Humphrey Bogart tells Ingrid Bergman
to get on that plane with Victor Laszlow even though Bogey loves her?

11:53.842 --> 11:55.256
What an ending!

11:55.256 --> 12:01.511
Well, there goes my need to finally see that one.

12:02.574 --> 12:06.551
He cares deeply for her and yet he lets her go.

12:06.551 --> 12:08.024
Wonder why Bogey did that?

12:08.024 --> 12:10.487
Why don't we put the movie in and find out?

12:10.487 --> 12:13.350
Because Laszlow needed her by his side to fight the Nazis.

12:13.350 --> 12:15.620
Forget the Nazis.

12:15.620 --> 12:17.968
No man in his right mind would give up Ingrid Bergman.

12:17.968 --> 12:23.734
Oh sure!  Sacrifice the entire free world for a little Swedish meatball?

12:23.734 --> 12:28.691
Look, I don't like Nazis any more than the next guy but what's Ingrid going to do with Laszlow?

12:28.691 --> 12:29.990
You're missing the point.

12:29.990 --> 12:37.768
What makes the movie so romantic is seeing Bogey go from a cynical playboy to a noble self-sacrificing patriot.

12:37.768 --> 12:42.175
Oh why don't you just put on some trenchcoats and act it out?

12:42.175 --> 12:45.207
I'm telling you, if you're in his shoes you've only got one choice.

12:45.207 --> 12:48.166
I'll say you do.  You get the hell down to the airport and tell her to get off the plane.

12:48.166 --> 12:50.445
She's going to Lisbon to fight the Nazis!

12:50.445 --> 12:54.801
No, she's not.  She's going to Chicago to turn a Country & Western station into an all-talk format.

12:54.801 --> 12:56.261
Where are you going?

12:56.261 --> 12:57.972
To stop Kate from getting on that plane!

12:57.972 --> 13:00.289
Well your date's gonna be here in a minute.  What are we supposed to tell her?

13:00.289 --> 13:03.447
Oh, I don't know.  Tell her I'm visiting a sick friend or something.

13:03.447 --> 13:05.212
Better yet ?just tell her the truth.

13:05.212 --> 13:07.641
Sometimes two people just aren't meant to be together.

13:07.641 --> 13:11.788
Ooh ?it's just like Redford and Streisand at the end of "The Way We Were."

13:11.788 --> 13:16.358
And that's another one down.

13:26.420 --> 13:27.463
Frasier!

13:27.463 --> 13:29.478
Don't say anything.  Just listen.

13:29.478 --> 13:34.147
Kate, this afternoon I wanted to say something to you but when I found out you were leaving I held back.

13:34.147 --> 13:37.065
Well, I'm not holding back any more.

13:37.065 --> 13:39.310
I can't stop thinking about you.

13:39.310 --> 13:44.222
Not just about the times we made love but about the possibility that we might have a future together.

13:44.222 --> 13:49.519
Now if there's any part of you that wonders the same thing about me,
we owe it to ourselves to see it through.

13:49.519 --> 13:53.258
You see, if you get on that plane tonight you'll regret it.

13:53.258 --> 13:57.117
Maybe not today, maybe not tomorrow, but soon

13:57.117 --> 13:59.956
and for the rest of our lives.

13:59.956 --> 14:04.557
Anyway I think I made my point.

14:04.557 --> 14:06.869
What do you think?

14:06.869 --> 14:09.689
Kate!

14:09.689 --> 14:14.605
More importantly, what do you think?

14:20.169 --> 14:24.150
Aw, for God's sake, you've been bawling the whole movie.

14:24.150 --> 14:28.332
I have not ?my eyes just itch!

14:29.083 --> 14:33.777
Well, it turns out Bogey was right to let her go.

14:33.777 --> 14:35.525
Frasier, what are you doing here?

14:35.525 --> 14:38.646
Look, Donna stayed to watch "Casablanca?with us.

14:38.646 --> 14:39.681
Donna, hi.

14:39.681 --> 14:41.627
Hello, Frasier.  How's your friend?

14:41.627 --> 14:43.541
In the hospital?

14:43.541 --> 14:47.843
Oh, he's doing much better actually.  They're thinking of sending him home tomorrow.

14:47.843 --> 14:51.227
After a heart transplant?

14:51.227 --> 14:55.708
Well, he's with an HMO!

14:55.708 --> 14:58.954
So... er... what do you say we have that dinner?

14:58.954 --> 15:03.554
Great, I'll just grab my coat.

15:04.623 --> 15:06.179
Kate!

15:06.179 --> 15:10.339
OK; now you listen to me.  I was so touched by what you just said at my apartment.

15:10.339 --> 15:13.834
You said everything that I've wanted to say to you for the last two months.

15:13.834 --> 15:16.577
Tony's just a guy that I went out with a couple of times.

15:16.577 --> 15:20.612
He just came over to say goodbye to me before I went to the airport.

15:20.612 --> 15:23.405
When you saw him you just looked so hurt...

15:23.405 --> 15:27.924
You had a date with her tonight too?

15:27.924 --> 15:30.155
...but apparently you rebounded!

15:30.155 --> 15:34.764
I'm sorry.  I thought you were sincere. Hold the elevator!

15:34.764 --> 15:37.146
Kate!  I was, Kate!  This woman means nothing to me.

15:37.146 --> 15:38.948
Thanks a lot!

15:38.948 --> 15:41.132
Oh, I'm sorry, Donna.  I'm truly sorry.

15:41.132 --> 15:44.009
It was very inconsiderate, but that woman means a great deal to me.

15:44.009 --> 15:47.011
I'm sure you'll hate me, but I just gotta do what I gotta do.

15:47.011 --> 15:48.992
I'm really sorry about this.

15:48.992 --> 15:51.188
Why don't you stay and watch the end of the movie.

15:51.188 --> 15:57.033
Thank you, but I've spent quite enough time in this house tonight.

16:01.865 --> 16:06.747
... this is lucky.  We can ride down together.

16:08.871 --> 16:10.957
IT'S HARD TO SAY GOODBYE IF YOU WON'T LEAVE

16:10.957 --> 16:12.686
Kate!

16:12.686 --> 16:13.900
Frasier!

16:13.900 --> 16:17.497
Oh my God.  I know you're upset.

16:17.497 --> 16:19.771
I don't even care about that woman.

16:19.771 --> 16:22.289
She's just a blind date I didn't even want to go on.
I wanted to be with you tonight.

16:22.289 --> 16:26.926
I know.  I overreacted.  I've been standing here for a half an hour hoping you'd come.

16:26.926 --> 16:28.194
I never thought you'd come.

16:28.194 --> 16:30.166
I can't believe I waited so long when all I had to do was say something.

16:30.166 --> 16:34.599
Listen, it's not your fault.  I could have said something.

16:35.061 --> 16:36.173
Well it doesn't matter.  We're together now.

16:36.173 --> 16:38.142
Your boarding pass, please?

16:38.142 --> 16:40.591
Go ahead.  Go ahead.

16:40.591 --> 16:42.172
Couldn't you just stay one more night?

16:42.172 --> 16:43.862
Just call them.  Tell them you'll come in tomorrow.

16:43.862 --> 16:46.294
I can't.  I can't.  I have a board meeting in the morning.

16:46.294 --> 16:49.089
Oh damn.  All right I'll call you.  Where are you staying?

16:49.089 --> 16:53.708
I'm staying at The Drake.  But, you know what?  I'll call you.  I'll call you the minute I get in.

16:53.708 --> 16:55.671
Ma'am, we're closing the doors.

16:55.671 --> 16:58.447
Goodbye

16:58.447 --> 16:59.566
I'll miss you.

16:59.566 --> 17:01.611
I'll miss you.

